This Package contains:
* ipy_flora/rpsimple.py
  * a simple interface between flora2 and python
* ipy_flora/ipy_flora.py
  * extends IPython for usage of rpsimple
* test_tutorial.py
  * tests if installation is correct
  * contains help on how to use flora2 within (i)python


Expects to have:
* IPython
   => http://ipython.scipy.org/
  or
   sudo aptitude install ipython
   (should be in your ubuntu/debian-repository)
* XSB
   => http://xsb.sourceforge.net/
  or
   sudo aptitude install xsb
   from
   deb http://autopoiesis.foi.hr/ubuntu ./
* Flora2
   => http://flora.sourceforge.net/
  or
   sudo aptitude install flora2
   from
   deb http://autopoiesis.foi.hr/ubuntu ./
* ReasonablePy
   => http://sourceforge.net/projects/reasonablepy/
  or 
   => https://github.com/johannesloetzsch/reasonablepy


Test without Installing:
* start IPython and enter
  [IPython]> _ip.load('ipy_flora')
* …use it…


Installation:
* sudo ./setup.py install
* add the line
	ip.load('ipy_flora.ipy_flora')
  to your ~/.ipython/ipy_user_conf.py


Usage:
* see: ./test_tutorial.py
